  "description": "This dataset comprises high-density functional near-infrared spectroscopy (fNIRS) measurements acquired during a Word-Color Stroop task. The study compares high-density multi-distance fNIRS configurations with sparse fNIRS approaches to evaluate their relative sensitivity in detecting brain activity during cognitive control tasks. Data were collected from multiple participants with concurrent behavioral performance metrics.",
  "methods_description": "High-density multi-distance fNIRS was used to acquire brain activity measurements during a Word-Color Stroop task. The study employed both high-density and sparse fNIRS configurations to compare detection sensitivity of brain activity.",
